  "texts": [
    "The Google Scholar search entry titles were then screened for relevance.",
    "Because the search entries are sorted by relevance, the screening process stopped when the titles ceased being relevant to the aim of the paper.",
    "In other words, not all 14,400, 11,200 and 9,340 entries were screened.",
    "After the Google Scholar screening, a total of 22 papers were included for the next screening process, which was abstract relevance.Before the abstract screening process, duplicates were tested through Zotero from all three databases.",
    "It was found that there were a number of duplicate papers which were subsequently removed."
